MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
For the GS-09:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience equivalent to the next lower grade level (GS-07) or pay band in the federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector analyzing the legal impact of legislative developments and administrative and judicial decisions, opinions, determinations, and rulings on agency programs; conducting research for the preparation of legal opinions on matters of interest to the agency; performing substantive legal analysis; and effectively communicating legal research and suggested resolutions in a clear, concise form. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
1) Analyzing legal case materials;
2) Interpreting technical material, rules, regulations, and instructions;
3) Presenting controversial or sensitive information in a clear, convincing, articulate manner;
4) Producing legal documents in a clear, concise, organized, and convincing manner for the intended audience, using correct English grammar, punctuation, and spelling;
5) Identifying and analyzing legal issues to recommend effective solutions;
6) Interviewing potential witnesses and preparing summary interview reports for attorney review;
7) Preparing and organizing case exhibits or master's or equivalent graduate degree or 2 full years of progressively higher level graduate education leading to such a degree or LL.B. or J.D., if related For the GS-07:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience equivalent to the next lower grade level (GS-05) or pay band in the federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector analyzing the legal impact of legislative developments and administrative and judicial decisions, opinions, determinations, and rulings on agency programs; conducting research for the preparation of legal opinions on matters of interest to the agency; performing substantive legal analysis; and effectively communicating legal research and suggested resolutions in a clear, concise form. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
1) Reviewing legal case materials to become familiar with cases;
2) Interpreting technical material, rules, regulations, and instructions;
3) Presenting controversial or sensitive information in a clear, convincing, articulate manner;
4) Producing written information in a clear, concise, organized, and convincing manner for the intended audience, using correct English grammar, punctuation, and spelling;
5) Preparing summaries of testimony and depositions. or 1 full year of graduate level education or superior academic achievement, if related. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
